        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 3:12PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 312 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 25
miles north of Ute Park, or 33 miles west of Raton, moving southeast
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vermejo Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
